<!-- SCHEMA: FAQPage (AEO) -->
<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a good CRS score for Canada Express Entry in 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A CRS score of 470 or above is competitive for all-program Express Entry draws in 2026. Recent draw cutoffs have ranged from 470 to 525. French-language and PNP-specific draws have lower cutoffs, sometimes under 400."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the CRS score calculated?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CRS score is calculated across four sections: Section A — core human capital (age, education, language, Canadian work experience, max 500 pts); Section B — spouse/partner factors (max 40 pts); Section C — skill transferability (max 100 pts); Section D — additional points including provincial nomination (+600), job offer (+50/+200), French bonus, Canadian education, and sibling in Canada. Maximum total is 1,200 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many CRS points does a provincial nomination give?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A provincial nomination (PNP) adds 600 CRS points instantly, virtually guaranteeing an ITA in the next Express Entry draw."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the minimum CRS score needed to get an ITA?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"There is no fixed minimum. All-program draw cutoffs have ranged from 470 to 525. Aim for 470+ for general draws. French-language draws can go as low as 371."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I calculate my CRS score without an IRCC account?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. This free CRS calculator requires no IRCC login. Enter your details and get an instant score — no data is stored."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I improve my CRS score?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Key ways to improve your CRS score: (1) Improve IELTS/CELPIP language scores — each CLB band can add 10–32 pts; (2) Get a provincial nomination (+600 pts); (3) Gain a Canadian job offer (+50 to +200 pts); (4) Obtain Canadian work experience; (5) Improve French language skills for a bonus of 25–50 pts."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this CRS calculator accurate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, this calculator uses the official IRCC CRS grid and is updated for 2026. Results are estimates and should be verified using the official IRCC CRS tool before submitting your Express Entry profile."}}]}</script>

