<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero" aria-label="CRS Calculator Hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h1>CRS Calculator 2026<br>Free Canada Express Entry Score Tool</h1>
    <p>Calculate your Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score instantly. Full section breakdown — no IRCC login required.</p>
    <div class="hero-badges">
      <span class="badge">✓ Updated 2026</span>
      <span class="badge">✓ Official IRCC Grid</span>
      <span class="badge">✓ 100% Free</span>
      <span class="badge">✓ No Login</span>
      <span class="badge">✓ Instant Results</span>
    </div>
    <a href="#calculator" class="hero-btn">Calculate My CRS Score →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- MAIN -->
<main id="main-content">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="grid">

      <!-- LEFT COLUMN -->
      <div>

        <!-- ===== CALCULATOR ===== -->
        <section class="card" id="calculator" aria-labelledby="calc-h">
          <h2 class="card-ttl" id="calc-h">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="4" y="2" width="16" height="20" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="10" x2="16" y2="10"/><line x1="8" y1="14" x2="16" y2="14"/><line x1="8" y1="18" x2="12" y2="18"/></svg>
            CRS Score Calculator — Canada Express Entry 2026
          </h2>
          <p style="font-size:.84rem;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:18px;">Enter your details below to <strong>calculate your CRS score</strong> instantly. Based on the official <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/eligibility/criteria-comprehensive-ranking-system.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRCC Comprehensive Ranking System grid</a>.</p>

          <form id="crsForm" onsubmit="doCalc(event)" novalidate>

            <div class="sec-hdr">Section A — Core Human Capital Factors</div>

            <div class="row2">
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="age">Age <span aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
                <select id="age" class="ctrl" required>
                  <option value="">— Select age —</option>
                  <option value="17u">17 or under</option>
                  <option value="18">18</option><option value="19">19</option><option value="20">20</option>
                  <option value="21">21</option><option value="22">22</option><option value="23">23</option>
                  <option value="24">24</option><option value="25">25</option><option value="26">26</option>
                  <option value="27">27</option><option value="28">28</option><option value="29">29</option>
                  <option value="30">30</option><option value="31">31</option><option value="32">32</option>
                  <option value="33">33</option><option value="34">34</option><option value="35">35</option>
                  <option value="36">36</option><option value="37">37</option><option value="38">38</option>
                  <option value="39">39</option><option value="40">40</option><option value="41">41</option>
                  <option value="42">42</option><option value="43">43</option><option value="44">44</option>
                  <option value="45p">45 or older</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="edu">Education Level <span aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
                <select id="edu" class="ctrl" required>
                  <option value="">— Select education —</option>
                  <option value="0">Less than secondary (high school)</option>
                  <option value="1">Secondary diploma</option>
                  <option value="2">1-year post-secondary program</option>
                  <option value="3">2-year post-secondary program</option>
                  <option value="4">Bachelor's degree / 3+ year program</option>
                  <option value="5">Two or more degrees (one 3+ yrs)</option>
                  <option value="6">Master's degree or professional degree</option>
                  <option value="7">Doctoral degree (PhD)</option>
                </select>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Marital / Partnership Status</label>
              <div class="radios">
                <label><input type="radio" name="marital" value="single" checked onchange="toggleSpouse(this)"> Single / Divorced / Widowed</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="marital" value="married" onchange="toggleSpouse(this)"> Married / Common-law</label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="form-g" id="spouseGroup">
              <label>Is your spouse/partner coming to Canada with you?</label>
              <div class="radios">
                <label><input type="radio" name="spouseComing" value="yes" checked onchange="toggleSpouseSection()"> Yes</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="spouseComing" value="no" onchange="toggleSpouseSection()"> No</label>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="form-g">
              <label for="canExp">Canadian Work Experience</label>
              <select id="canExp" class="ctrl">
                <option value="0">None</option>
                <option value="1">1 year</option><option value="2">2 years</option>
                <option value="3">3 years</option><option value="4">4 years</option>
                <option value="5">5 or more years</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="sec-hdr">Section B — First Official Language</div>

            <div class="form-g">
              <label for="langTest">Language Test Type</label>
              <select id="langTest" class="ctrl">
                <option value="ielts">IELTS (English)</option>
                <option value="celpip">CELPIP (English)</option>
                <option value="tef">TEF Canada (French)</option>
                <option value="tcf">TCF Canada (French)</option>
              </select>
              <div class="hint">Convert your IELTS/CELPIP band to CLB using our <a href="/ielts-crs-calculator">IELTS to CRS converter</a>.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="row2">
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="lsp">Speaking (CLB)</label>
                <select id="lsp" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9</option><option value="10">CLB 10+</option></select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="ll">Listening (CLB)</label>
                <select id="ll" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9</option><option value="10">CLB 10+</option></select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="lr">Reading (CLB)</label>
                <select id="lr" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9</option><option value="10">CLB 10+</option></select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="lw">Writing (CLB)</label>
                <select id="lw" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9</option><option value="10">CLB 10+</option></select>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sec-hdr">Section C — Second Official Language (Optional)</div>

            <div class="form-g">
              <label for="l2test">Second Language Test</label>
              <select id="l2test" class="ctrl" onchange="toggleL2(this)">
                <option value="none">None / Not applicable</option>
                <option value="ielts">IELTS</option><option value="celpip">CELPIP</option>
                <option value="tef">TEF Canada</option><option value="tcf">TCF Canada</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="row2" id="lang2Fields">
              <div class="form-g"><label>Speaking (CLB)</label><select id="l2sp" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6+</option></select></div>
              <div class="form-g"><label>Listening (CLB)</label><select id="l2ll" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6+</option></select></div>
              <div class="form-g"><label>Reading (CLB)</label><select id="l2lr" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6+</option></select></div>
              <div class="form-g"><label>Writing (CLB)</label><select id="l2lw" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4 or less</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6+</option></select></div>
            </div>

            <!-- SPOUSE -->
            <div id="spouseSection">
              <div class="sec-hdr">Section D — Spouse / Partner Factors</div>
              <div class="row2">
                <div class="form-g">
                  <label for="spEdu">Spouse Education</label>
                  <select id="spEdu" class="ctrl"><option value="0">Less than secondary</option><option value="1">Secondary</option><option value="2">1-year program</option><option value="3">2-year program</option><option value="4">Bachelor's / 3+ yr</option><option value="5">Two or more degrees</option><option value="6">Master's</option><option value="7">PhD</option></select>
                </div>
                <div class="form-g">
                  <label for="spCanExp">Spouse Canadian Work Exp</label>
                  <select id="spCanExp" class="ctrl"><option value="0">None</option><option value="1">1 year</option><option value="2">2 years</option><option value="3">3 years</option><option value="4">4 years</option><option value="5">5+ years</option></select>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="form-g">
                <label for="spLangTest">Spouse Language Test</label>
                <select id="spLangTest" class="ctrl" onchange="toggleSpLang(this)"><option value="none">None</option><option value="ielts">IELTS</option><option value="celpip">CELPIP</option><option value="tef">TEF Canada</option></select>
              </div>
              <div class="row2" id="spouseLangFields">
                <div class="form-g"><label>Speaking (CLB)</label><select id="spLsp" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4-</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9+</option></select></div>
                <div class="form-g"><label>Listening (CLB)</label><select id="spLll" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4-</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9+</option></select></div>
                <div class="form-g"><label>Reading (CLB)</label><select id="spLlr" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4-</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9+</option></select></div>
                <div class="form-g"><label>Writing (CLB)</label><select id="spLlw" class="ctrl"><option value="4">CLB 4-</option><option value="5">CLB 5</option><option value="6">CLB 6</option><option value="7">CLB 7</option><option value="8">CLB 8</option><option value="9">CLB 9+</option></select></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sec-hdr">Section E — Skill Transferability</div>

            <div class="form-g">
              <label for="fgnExp">Foreign Work Experience</label>
              <select id="fgnExp" class="ctrl"><option value="0">None</option><option value="1">1–2 years</option><option value="2">3 or more years</option></select>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Foreign education + language CLB 7+?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="eduLang" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="eduLang" value="1"> Yes</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Certificate of qualification (trade occupation)?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="tradesCert" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="tradesCert" value="1"> Yes</label></div>
            </div>

            <div class="sec-hdr">Section F — Additional Points</div>

            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Provincial Nomination (PNP)?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="pnp" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="pnp" value="600"> Yes (+600 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Valid job offer — NOC TEER 0 Major Group 00?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="jo1" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="jo1" value="200"> Yes (+200 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Valid job offer — NOC TEER 0, 1, 2 or 3 (other)?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="jo2" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="jo2" value="50"> Yes (+50 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Sibling in Canada (citizen or PR)?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="sib" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="sib" value="15"> Yes (+15 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>French CLB 7+ with English CLB 4 or less?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="fr1" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="fr1" value="25"> Yes (+25 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>French CLB 7+ with English CLB 5 or higher?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="fr2" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="fr2" value="50"> Yes (+50 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Canadian post-secondary education — 1–2 year program?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="cedu1" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="cedu1" value="15"> Yes (+15 pts)</label></div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-g">
              <label>Canadian post-secondary education — 3+ year program?</label>
              <div class="radios"><label><input type="radio" name="cedu2" value="0" checked> No</label><label><input type="radio" name="cedu2" value="30"> Yes (+30 pts)</label></div>
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="btn-calc">🧮 Calculate My CRS Score →</button>
          </form>
        </section>

        <!-- RESULTS -->
        <section id="results" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
          <div class="res-card">
            <h2 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin-bottom:14px">Your CRS Score Result</h2>
            <div class="score-wrap">
              <span class="score-num" id="scoreNum">0</span>
              <div class="score-lbl">out of 1,200 possible points</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bar-wrap"><div class="bar" id="scoreBar" style="width:0%"></div></div>
            <div class="verdict" id="scoreVerdict"></div>
            <div class="bk-tbl">
              <table>
                <thead><tr><th>CRS Factor</th><th class="pts" style="text-align:right">Points</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody id="bkTbody"></tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <div class="res-acts">
              <button class="btn-act pri" onclick="window.print()">🖨 Print / Save PDF</button>
              <button class="btn-act" onclick="copyScore()">📋 Copy Score</button>
              <button class="btn-act" onclick="shareWA()">💬 Share via WhatsApp</button>
            </div>
            <div class="imp-cta">
              <span class="ico">📈</span>
              <div>
                <h4>Want a higher CRS score?</h4>
                <p>10 proven strategies to boost your Comprehensive Ranking System points fast.</p>
                <a href="/how-to-improve-crs-score">Read the CRS Score Improvement Guide →</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- WHAT IS CRS -->
        <section class="info" aria-labelledby="what-crs">
          <h2 id="what-crs">What is CRS Score? (Comprehensive Ranking System)</h2>
          <p>The <strong>Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS)</strong> is a points-based ranking system used by <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)</a> to rank candidates in the <strong>Express Entry pool</strong>. Your CRS score is determined by human capital factors — age, education, language proficiency, and Canadian work experience. The higher your score, the stronger your chances of receiving an Invitation to Apply (ITA) for permanent residence.</p>
          <p>Scores range from 0 to 1,200 points. IRCC conducts regular <a href="/express-entry-draw-results">Express Entry draws</a> inviting the highest-scoring candidates. Use our free <strong>CRS calculator</strong> to estimate your score and understand exactly which factors to improve. For a full explanation see our <a href="/what-is-crs-score">What is CRS Score guide</a>.</p>

          <h3>CRS Score Range &amp; PR Chances</h3>
          <table class="dt" role="table">
            <thead><tr><th>CRS Score Range</th><th>PR Chances</th><th>Typical Draw Eligibility</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Below 400</strong></td><td>Very Low</td><td>Not competitive for most draws</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>400 – 450</strong></td><td>Low–Moderate</td><td>May qualify for PNP-specific draws</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>451 – 470</strong></td><td>Moderate</td><td>Getting close to all-program cutoffs</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>471 – 500</strong></td><td>Good</td><td>Competitive for all-program draws</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>500+</strong></td><td>Excellent</td><td>Very strong — likely to receive ITA</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

        <!-- HOW TO USE -->
        <section class="info" aria-labelledby="how-use">
          <h2 id="how-use">How to Use This Free CRS Calculator</h2>
          <div class="steps">
            <div class="step"><div class="step-n">1</div><div class="step-t"><h4>Enter Personal Details</h4><p>Age, education, marital status and Canadian work experience — the core human capital factors.</p></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-n">2</div><div class="step-t"><h4>Add Language Scores</h4><p>Select your test (IELTS, CELPIP, TEF, TCF) and enter CLB levels. Need help? Use our <a href="/ielts-crs-calculator">IELTS to CLB converter</a>.</p></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-n">3</div><div class="step-t"><h4>Add Additional Points</h4><p>Include provincial nomination, job offer, French bonus or Canadian education if applicable.</p></div></div>
            <div class="step"><div class="step-n">4</div><div class="step-t"><h4>Get Instant Results</h4><p>Click Calculate to see your total CRS score with a full section breakdown and improvement tips.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- HOW CALCULATED -->
        <section class="info" aria-labelledby="how-calc">
          <h2 id="how-calc">How is CRS Score Calculated? Full Breakdown</h2>
          <p>The CRS score is calculated using the <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/eligibility/criteria-comprehensive-ranking-system.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official IRCC CRS criteria</a>. Maximum is <strong>1,200 points</strong> across four sections:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Section A — Core Human Capital (max 500 pts):</strong> Age, education, first official language (4 skills), second language, and Canadian work experience. This section differs slightly if you have an accompanying spouse.</li>
            <li><strong>Section B — Spouse/Partner Factors (max 40 pts):</strong> Spouse's education level, language test scores, and Canadian work experience — only when your spouse is accompanying you to Canada.</li>
            <li><strong>Section C — Skill Transferability (max 100 pts):</strong> Combinations of foreign work experience + language proficiency, education + language, and trade certification. See our <a href="/cec-crs-calculator">CEC CRS calculator</a> for the Canadian Experience Class grid.</li>
            <li><strong>Section D — Additional Points (max 600 pts):</strong> Provincial nomination (+600), <a href="/pnp-crs-calculator">PNP stream</a> job offer (+200 or +50), French language bonus (+25 or +50), Canadian post-secondary education (+15 or +30), sibling in Canada (+15).</li>
          </ul>
          <p>For the full points table, visit our <a href="/how-crs-is-calculated">How CRS Score is Calculated guide</a> or check the <a href="https://ircc.canada.ca/english/immigrate/skilled/crs-tool.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official IRCC CRS tool</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- FAQ -->
        <section class="info" aria-labelledby="faq-h">
          <h2 id="faq-h">Frequently Asked Questions — CRS Score Calculator</h2>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">What is a good CRS score for Canada Express Entry in 2026?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">A CRS score of <strong>470 or above</strong> is competitive for all-program Express Entry draws. Recent 2025 cutoffs ranged from 471 to 525. <a href="/pnp-crs-calculator">PNP-specific draws</a> and French-language draws have lower cutoffs — sometimes under 400. Use our <a href="/crs-cutoff-scores">CRS cutoff scores history</a> to track trends.</div></div>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">How is the CRS score calculated?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">CRS score is calculated across four sections: (A) Core human capital — age, education, language, <a href="/cec-crs-calculator">Canadian work experience</a>; (B) Spouse/partner factors; (C) Skill transferability — foreign work exp + language combinations; (D) Additional points including provincial nomination (+600) and job offer. Maximum total is 1,200 points. Read the full <a href="/how-crs-is-calculated">CRS calculation guide</a>.</div></div>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">How many CRS points does a provincial nomination give?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">A provincial nomination (PNP) adds <strong>600 CRS points</strong> instantly — virtually guaranteeing an ITA in the next Express Entry draw. Check which province best suits your profile using our <a href="/ontario-crs-calculator">Ontario CRS calculator</a> or <a href="/alberta-crs-calculator">Alberta CRS calculator</a>.</div></div>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">What is the minimum CRS score needed to get an ITA?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">There is no fixed minimum — the cutoff varies each draw. Recent all-program draw cutoffs ranged from 471 to 525. Aim for <strong>470+</strong> for competitive chances. Monitor live cutoffs on our <a href="/crs-cutoff-scores">Express Entry cutoff scores page</a>.</div></div>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">Can I calculate my CRS score without an IRCC account?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">Yes — this <strong>free CRS calculator</strong> requires no IRCC login, government account, or personal information. Enter your details and get an instant score. Your data is never stored. You can also verify results using the <a href="https://ircc.canada.ca/english/immigrate/skilled/crs-tool.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official IRCC CRS tool</a>.</div></div>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">Is this CRS calculator accurate?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">Yes — this calculator uses the official IRCC CRS grid updated for 2026. Results are estimates based on information you enter. Always verify using the <a href="https://ircc.canada.ca/english/immigrate/skilled/crs-tool.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official IRCC CRS tool</a> before submitting your Express Entry profile.</div></div>

          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)" aria-expanded="false">How can I improve my CRS score?<svg class="arr" width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button><div class="faq-a">Top strategies: (1) Improve IELTS/CELPIP scores — each CLB band adds 10–32 pts; (2) Get a Provincial Nomination (+600 pts); (3) Get a Canadian job offer (+50–200 pts); (4) Gain Canadian work experience; (5) Improve French language skills for a 25–50 pt bonus. See the full <a href="/how-to-improve-crs-score">CRS score improvement guide</a>.</div></div>
        </section>

